jpmorgan chase & co.
the provision for credit losses totaled $210million, up 2% from the prior year. the increase
was due to the merger but was largely offset by a lower provision for credit losses, reflecting
favorable credit trends.
noninterest expense increased by 68% to $490million, largely due to the merger.
