note 18  preferred stock
jpmorgan chase is authorized to issue 200million shares of preferred stock, in one or more
series, with a par value of $1 per share. outstanding preferred stock at december31, 2005 and
2004, was 280,433 and 4.28million shares, respectively. on may6, 2005, jpmorgan chase redeemed a
total of 4.0million shares of its fixed/adjustable rate, noncumulative preferred stock.
dividends on shares of the outstanding series of preferred stock are payable quarterly. the
preferred stock outstanding takes precedence over jpmorgan chases common stock for the payment of
dividends and the distribution of assets in the event of a liquidation or dissolution of the firm.
